<br>
On Vah Shir rogues:  Vah Shir have decent rogue stats, and a few nice advantages:  once you get your DE mask, you can shrink to a more reasonable size.  Also, they can do the Shar Vahl throwing weapon fletching quest... and a rogue who can make 12 damage 120 range throwing weapons is dangerous indeed (deadly strike for 100 at level 10, anyone?)  And they make good bakers.<br>
<br>
A warning on being a rogue: you have to love being one to play the class right.  I've seen too many twinkie PL rogues who drop out fast and hard, thinking the class stinks.  We don't solo, and many of our abilities are related to exploration, not combat, though we can break out the heavy damage when we want to.  If you want to be curious, and go adventuring, and do wacky things just because you're a rogue and that arbitrarily gives you the power to be insane (whatcha doin Jarkell?  Oh, just exploring lower guk... hey look a big hand!  whatcha doin' now?  Disarming that stupid trap in sol b, it's too loud and annoying!  How about now?  Oh, going LFG as an iksar ranger, why?)<br>
<br>
